comment: Definition *14.01 in [WhiteheadRussell] p. 184. In Principia Mathematica, Russell and Whitehead define ` iota ` in terms of a function of ` ( iota x ph ) ` . Their definition differs in that a function of ` ( iota x ph ) ` evaluates to "false" when there isn't a single ` x ` that satisfies ` ph ` . (Contributed by Andrew Salmon, 11-Jul-2011.)
